  "description": "I\u0026rsquo;m having a conversation with Microsoft Copilot on my Omnibook, about Teraum, and it babbled a lot of nonsense but led me to the idea that stories of Teraum (including the RPG sessions/campaigns) should encourage genre as ontological method for interpreting narrative, which informs\u0026hellip; I guess I\u0026rsquo;d call it karmic orientation, which informs how well things will go for that character (\u0026ldquo;well\u0026rdquo; being relative to their karma).\nI hadn\u0026rsquo;t thought about it but I guess I just use a karmic system for Teraum, but I should really give that some more detailed thought.\n",
